              "type": "output_text",
              "text": "To solve $17 \\times 19$, we can use a few different mental math strategies:\n\n1.  **Method 1: Difference of Squares**\n    Notice that both numbers are equidistant from $18$ ($17$ is $18 - 1$ and $19$ is $18 + 1$). \n    We can use the formula $(a - b)(a + b) = a^2 - b^2$:\n    $(18 - 1)(18 + 1) = 18^2 - 1^2$\n    Since $18^2 = 324$ and $1^2 = 1$:\n    $324 - 1 = 323$\n\n2.  **Method 2: Distributive Property**\n    You can break the multiplication down by treating $19$ as $(20 - 1)$:\n    $17 \\times (20 - 1) = (17 \\times 20) - (17 \\times 1)$\n    $17 \\times 20 = 340$\n    $340 - 17 = 323$\n\nBoth methods confirm that $17 \\times 19 = 323$.\n\n323",
